	   <tr><td colspan=2>I got this on The Nameless Server from a low level Druid who got it from a GM event.&nbsp;&nbsp;He said he got it for dying the most.  LOL  At the time NEITHER of us knew what this was or how rare an item it was.  (I SWEAR!!!)  <br><br>I traded him enough +WIS gear to get his WIS up 10 points (about 600pp worth, before Othmir Fur Caps were 60pp in Bazaar) and actually dropped my WIS by 2.<br>  <br>I almost feel bad, except it really was a good trade if you exclude the rarity of the item.  And, well, the skill mod...which was useless to me til i hit 51.  I was already maxxed. (IMHO - it's a silly skill mod: Any caster/priest class that uses, actually USES spells will sit and med enough in the first 2 or 3 hours at a new level to max the skill for that level.  So, what's the point really?  But that's just my opinion...)<br><br>I know I saw it in Bazaar as well.  So, one can conclude that there are at least two on The Nameless.  Someone was selling it for 17kpp.  I about messed myself.  I am considering auctioning this off when I have used it to max all my meditating characters.  <br><br>Uilerin Cerriddwyn<br>51 Druid<br>The Nameless<br><br>PS: There is no graphic on it for Wood Elf Druids, don't know about others.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Sep 10 20:00:55 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
