	   <tr><td colspan=2>A report on a GM event that took Place on Cazic Thule on Wednesday May 15th<br><br>A battle between Good, Bringers of Light and Evil, Children of Darkness took place at the Gates of Freeport. Before the start of the Battle Knight Truheart called forth for players to join the Bringers of Light guild and lay waste to the forces that were approaching. Many characters of all shapes and sizes came forth to prove their allegiance to the light including myself. During this time, while roleplaying, I asked for and was granted some spys to be sent to East Commonlands where reports of the enemy were being sent from. This was confirmed as our spies reported that a Dark Elf General was calling forth Players of the Evil persuasion to come and join the Armies of Innoruuk and become his Children of Darkness. Once both sides had amassed their armies the CoD zoned into West Freeport and Began the Guild war with the Bringers.<br><br>The battle was long as the Children of Darkness found themselves protecting their General rather than attacking. They had not counted on the great number of Bringers that had amassed and with great teamwork and strategy and after a long battle the General of the CoD had been slain.<br><br>At this point Knight Truheart began summoning those players that had joined his battle since the beginning and who had helped to Bringers of Light the most in attaining their victory. Those who recieved rewards were Ointment, Faederya, Faedilist, Veschar, Timmyonous, Fineskin and Pcapone. Myself and Pcapone recieved the Guise of the Deciever mask, WHICH I LOVE!!, Faedilest, Veschar and Timmyonous recieved the Softbreeze Crown which had a 15% mod to meditation. Fineskin recieved a lusterous russet Breastplate and Helm and lastly Faederya recieved Lusterous russet Vambraces.<br><br>After Knight Truheart gave out his rewards Tilol, Thorikos and Lathia showed up to hand out other gifts and converse with players. Some killing still raged on at this point but many of the players had rejoined their old guilds by this point. All in all it was one of the best GM events I have ever participated in and I hope many more like this will be in the works. Also a special congrats to Faedilest and Fineskin who also were celebrating there EQ wedding day as well.<br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
