	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, May 21st 8:01 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.96]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The funniest part about this item is the fact that it's meditation skill mod becomes more and more worthless as you level.<br><br>Meditation is capped at 235 for casters until they hit level 51. Once you hit level 51, your meditation skill cap goes up to 252.<br><br>Since you can't have a higher &quot;modified&quot; skill over 252, the skill bonus on this item becomes comepletely useless at level 51 (or once your skill reaches 252).<br><br>If the skill mod gave a &quot;virtual boost&quot; over the cap, similar to the newer haste songs from Luclin, then skill mods would actually gain worth as you level.<br>If they &quot;rolled over the cap&quot;, at 252 natural skill, this item would boost your skill up to 289 or a 2 mana/tick improvement over what you have at 252 med rate. <br>&nbsp;<br>Jarnin Fisheermann<br>57th Evoker<br>&lt;Ring of Cobalt&gt;<br>Rallos Zek</td></tr>
